---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Industrial Saw Repair | Complete Blade Restoration Services"
  description="Professional industrial saw repair including tip replacement, tensioning, and geometry correction. Restore blades others have deemed unrepairable."
>
  <section class="gradient-hero text-white py-20">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold mb-6">Industrial Saw Repair</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-blue-100">
          Complete blade restoration including tip replacement, body repair, and precision tensioning.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="prose-custom">
        <h2>The Industrial Saw Repair Imperative</h2>
        <p>
          In high-stakes manufacturing environments, the condition of your cutting tools is a primary driver 
          of operational efficiency. An industrial saw represents significant capital investment, and its 
          performance is directly tied to blade health.
        </p>

        <h3>Technical Specifications We Restore</h3>
        <p>Effective repair begins with understanding the blade's original design parameters:</p>
        
        <h4>Tooth Geometry and Form</h4>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Tooth Pitch:</strong> Distance between teeth, dictating chip load per tooth</li>
          <li><strong>Gullet Depth:</strong> Chip evacuation space behind the cutting edge</li>
          <li><strong>Rake Angle:</strong> Controls cutting aggressiveness (positive, negative, or straight)</li>
          <li><strong>Set Pattern:</strong> Raker set or wavy set for proper kerf width</li>
        </ul>

        <h4>Blade Body Specifications</h4>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Material:</strong> HSS, TCT, Solid Carbide, or Bi-Metal substrates</li>
          <li><strong>Tension:</strong> Stretched to specific PSI to prevent deflection</li>
          <li><strong>Body Thickness:</strong> Checked for uniformity and flatness</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Specialized Repair Capabilities</h3>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">Tip Re-brazing</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Missing or cracked carbide tips removed, seat cleaned, new tips silver-brazed with controlled furnace process.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">Body Straightening</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Warped or stretched blade bodies restored to flatness for proper tracking.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">Crack Repair</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Body cracks stopped and repaired to prevent propagation and catastrophic failure.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">Re-tensioning</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Blades stretched to manufacturer specifications (25,000-35,000 PSI) for straight tracking.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h3>The CarbideSaws.com Difference</h3>
        <p>
          We routinely recover blades other shops have deemed "unrepairable" through our advanced 
          tip-indexing and metallurgical expertise. Our turnaround times are designed for production 
          schedules, not the other way around.
        </p>

        <h3>Professional Vendor Comparison</h3>
        <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl my-8 overflow-x-auto">
          <table class="w-full text-sm">
            <thead>
              <tr class="border-b-2 border-gray-200">
                <th class="text-left py-3 font-semibold text-primary">Vendor Type</th>
                <th class="text-left py-3 font-semibold text-primary">Best For</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="text-gray-700">
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-200">
                <td class="py-3 font-medium">Local Machine Shop</td>
                <td class="py-3">Non-critical, occasional use blades</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-200">
                <td class="py-3 font-medium">OEM Service Dept</td>
                <td class="py-3">Warranty repairs, proprietary designs</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="bg-blue-50">
                <td class="py-3 font-medium text-secondary">CarbideSaws.com</td>
                <td class="py-3">Production environments requiring maximum uptime</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-gray-50 py-16">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-primary mb-4">Have Damaged Blades?</h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-8">
        Send us blades others couldn't fix. We'll assess repairability at no charge.
      </p>
      <a href="/carbidesaws-rebuild/contact" class="bg-secondary text-white font-bold px-8 py-4 rounded-lg hover:bg-primary transition">
        Request Assessment
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
